<para>
List all currently open displays.</para>
<para>
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>display_manager</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> a <link linkend="GdkDisplayManager"><type>GdkDisplayManager</type></link> 
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&#160;:</term><listitem><simpara> a newly allocated <link linkend="GSList"><type>GSList</type></link> of <link linkend="GdkDisplay"><type>GdkDisplay</type></link> objects.
 Free this list with <link linkend="g-slist-free"><function>g_slist_free()</function></link> when you are done with it.

</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist><para role="since">Since 2.2</para></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="gdk-display-get-core-pointer" role="function" condition="since:2.2">
<title>gdk_display_get_core_pointer ()</title>
<indexterm zone="gdk-display-get-core-pointer" role="2.2"><primary sortas="display_get_core_pointer">gdk_display_get_core_pointer</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="GdkDevice">GdkDevice</link> *         gdk_display_get_core_pointer        (<link linkend="GdkDisplay">GdkDisplay</link> *display);</programlisting>
<para>
Returns the core pointer device for the given display</para>
<para>
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>display</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> a <link linkend="GdkDisplay"><type>GdkDisplay</type></link>
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&#160;:</term><listitem><simpara> the core pointer device; this is owned by the
  display and should not be freed.

</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist><para role="since">Since 2.2</para></refsect2>

